The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Telecast rights

New Delhi: Zee Sports on Monday announced the successful acquisition of broadcasting rights for the inaugural Afro-Asian Cup to be held later this month in South Africa. 

The $100,000 series, comprising three matches, has been officially recognised by the ICC. 

The rights, which cover the Indian sub-continent, are the first bagged by the channel for telecasting of cricket. 

The inaugural match will be held on August 17 in Centurion. The next two matches will be held at Sahara Stadium in Kings-mead on August 20 and 21. (PTI) 




